      <hedline>
        <hl1>INVESTMENT IN CHINA</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Foreign investment in China falls nearly 8 percent, to $22.79 billion, in first eight months of year compared with same period a year earlier (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Foreign investment in China fell nearly 8 percent, to $22.79 billion, in the first eight months of the year compared with the same period a year earlier, the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation said. But it said new contracts for investment not yet delivered rose 31.27 percent, to $33.25 billion, as foreign companies position themselves for what is expected to be a friendlier business climate after China joins the World Trade Organization. The country's W.T.O. membership is expected to be finalized this year.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
